P1.1 Pricing API Implementation Details:

PROBLEM:
- queryFargatePrice() in pricing.go was stubbed to return error
- Line 272 returned: 'pricing API response parsing not implemented'
- Cost estimates always fell back to hardcoded regional prices

SOLUTION:
- Implemented parsePricingResponse() to parse AWS Pricing API JSON
- AWS response structure:
  terms.OnDemand.<skuTermCode>.priceDimensions.<rateCode>.pricePerUnit.USD
- Added pricingResponse struct to unmarshal the nested JSON
- Extracts USD price string and converts to float64

ERROR HANDLING:
- Invalid JSON -> unmarshal error
- Missing terms.OnDemand -> 'no USD price found'
- Missing USD in pricePerUnit -> 'no USD price found'
- Invalid price format -> 'parse USD price' error

TESTING:
- 9 test cases in TestParsePricingResponse:
  - valid_fargate_cpu_pricing (0.04048)
  - valid_fargate_memory_pricing (0.004445)
  - multiple_terms_takes_first_price
  - invalid_json
  - missing_terms
  - empty_on_demand
  - missing_usd_price
  - invalid_price_format
  - zero_price_valid

FALLBACK BEHAVIOR UNCHANGED:
- If Pricing API call fails, getFargateFallbackPrices() is still used
- This ensures the system degrades gracefully
